By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) –  The latest COVID-19 report released by the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control has it that 152 new cases were confirmed on Sunday bringing the total confirmed cases to 65,148. It also said that 61,073 patients have been discharged since the index case was reported in Nigeria on February 27 2020 and 1,163 deaths recorded so far. The NCDC further informed that Lagos State, the epicentre of the infection accounted for 136 of the 152 of the cases. The report released via it’s twitter handle listed other states  where people tested positive as follows:Kano-4Niger-3Ekiti-2Kaduna-2Ogun-2Taraba-2FCT-1Similarly, the health  agency presented the states total confirmed cases as follows: By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - Nigeria Centre for Disease Control has confirmed 152 new cases of COVID-19 in Nigeria. According to the report released via it's twitter handle late Tuesday, this brings total confirmed cases 64,336 out ot which 60,333 have been treated and discharged from various isolation… November 11, 2020 In "Top Stories" ABUJA - Lagos State, the Federal Capital Territory, Kano and Oyo have spiked the number Nigeria's confirmed Coronavirus cases with the addition of 35 confirmed infections as at late Thursday night.Lagos State has 19 new infections with FCT contributing nine. Kano and Oyo have five and two new cases respectively… April 16, 2020 In "Top Stories" By Abujah Racheal ABUJA - The number of  COVID-19 patients discharged in the country  is now 13,447 following 344 new successfully treated cases. This is according to the new data released by the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) on its official twitter account on Sunday. The NCDC had also… July 13, 2020 In "Top Stories"